      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 51,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "STARTUP:\n1. KubernetesJob.add_mesh(\"replica0\", pod_spec)                    ← K8s API call\n2. Monarch Operator creates Pod replica0-0 with 8 GPUs             ← K8s schedules onto GPU node\n3. Pod starts run_worker_loop_forever() on tcp://:26600             ← Monarch worker ready\n4. OrchestrationManager gets HostMesh, passes to ReplicaActor       ← ReplicaActor HOLDS the HostMesh\n5. ReplicaActor._spawn_trainers(): host_mesh.spawn_procs(8)         ← creates ProcMesh on pod\n6. ReplicaActor spawns TrainingActors on ProcMesh                   ← Monarch actor RPC\n7. TrainingActors run trainer.train()                               ← Training begins\n\nINNER RETRY (process dies, pod alive — FAST):\n8.  GPU process dies → __supervise__ returns True                   ← fault stops at ReplicaActor\n9.  start_replica retry loop catches exception                      ← no teardown needed\n10. _spawn_trainers(): host_mesh.spawn_procs(8) again               ← same pod, new processes\n11. Re-spawn TrainingActors, resume training                        ← ~seconds recovery\n\nOUTER RETRY (pod dies — SLOW, fallback only):\n12. HostMesh is gone → inner retry fails → exception to controller  ← propagates up\n13. _teardown + _ensure_job_alive → recreate K8s job                ← new pod allocation\n14. New HostMesh → new ReplicaActor → go to step 5                  ← full respin",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
